-- Mexico Stocks: Pochteca, Grupo Mexico, Industrias Penoles
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-28T21:15:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/mexico-stocks-pochteca-grupo-mexico-industrias-and-penoles.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index fell 0.1 percent to 38,910.68.  Grupo Pochteca SAB (POCHTECB)  , the chemical maker
formerly known as Dermet de Mexico, jumped 7.5 percent to 2.14
pesos. The company said earnings before interest, taxes,
depreciation and amortization were 41 million pesos ($3.2
million) in the first quarter, according to preliminary results
sent yesterday to the Mexican stock exchange. Preliminary first-
quarter sales were 1 billion pesos.  Grupo Mexico  SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, declined 1.5 percent to 40.23 pesos. Copper
declined in  New York  on signs that demand for the metal is
weakening in  China , the world’s biggest consumer.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PENOLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), the nation’s biggest
silver producer and a miner of gold, fell 1.2 percent to 615.54
pesos. Gold futures fell as a strike by jewelers in  India , the
world’s biggest buyer, curbed demand. Silver also slumped.  To contact the reporter on this story:
